 更多收起网络短语

completely [ kəm'pli:tli ]

  • adv.
    • to a complete degree or to the full or entire extent (`whole' is often used informally for `wholly')

      "it was completely different from what we expected"; " was completely at fault"

      同义词： wholly entirely totally all altogether whole

    • so as to be complete; with everything necessary

      "he had filled out the form completely"; " the apartment was completely furnished"

以上来源于: WordNet

    • [美国俚语]很，太，极

同近义词同根词

  • adv. 完全地，彻底地；完整地

    • entirely , totally , thoroughly , fully , absolutely , strictly , perfectly

词根： complete

adj.

complete 完整的；完全的；彻底的

completed 完整的；完全的

n.

completion 完成，结束；实现

completeness 完整；完全；完成；圆满；结束

v.

completed 完成（complete的过去分词）

vt.

complete 完成
